description:
The appointee will report to the System Engineering Services Manager and is responsible for network infrastructure planning, implementation, administration monitoring and trouble shooting.  Your prerequisite attributes are:

University/Tertiary graduate in related disciplines;
At least 3 years’ experience in Windows Server and network configuration and administration;
In-depth network knowledge and solid hands-on experience in firewall, routers and switches;
Experience in VCP is an advantage.

We offer competitive remuneration plus comprehensive fringe benefits.  Interested parties, please send full resume and salary expected to Senior Human Resources Officer, Meyer Aluminium Ltd, 5 Dai Li Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, Tai Po, New Territories.  or clicking "Apply Now'.  All applications will be treated in strictly confidential.

Company Overview

Mizuho has a long-term commitment to the Hong Kong market. With strong ties to Mizuho’s global network and a workforce of over 600 staff in Hong Kong, we are able to help corporations in Hong Kong to expand their business worldwide. Our clients primarily comprise Japanese and non-Japanese corporations (including those domiciled in the PRC), financial institutions, and government and quasi-government organizations. We provide a full spectrum of corporate banking services to our customers including syndicated loans, treasury, transaction banking, financial advisory, project finance, merger and acquisition, leveraged finance, and structured finance.

Why Mizuho

At Mizuho, we provide the stability of an international industry leader with the career trajectory of a growing business. Our steady, strategic growth gives our people at all levels rewarding degrees of responsibility and a richer work experience than a boutique firm or an established giant could offer alone.

It is the local expertise of our employees that makes our global network so powerful. By collaborating with colleagues and clients who have your same ambition and drive, you can amplify your sphere of influence and base of knowledge as part of one of the largest—and growing—banks in the world.

About the Team

Systems Planning & Development Section (SPD) is responsible for overall system planning of Hong Kong office, EUC/RPA development, PoC for new system solution, and security control. System Security Control Team is mainly responsible for conducting user ID and access authority control, system security monitoring, software license control, database management, firewall management, penetration test and follow up, coordinate assessment for regulatory requirement, support Head office and local system projects and follow up the revision of system security policy, guideline and let related staff to understand them.

Role requirements

To assume a team lead position to manage all-round Cybersecurity function for the Bank
To identify potential threats of and report on security violations and control weaknesses in cybersecurity by determining causes, possible solutions and remedial actions required for ensuring data security;
To recommend and implement changes to procedures and systems designed to enhance systems security;
To develop and conduct IT security awareness training programs for all units within the Bank and ensure IT security/risk compliance within the bank;
To develop and maintain the system security procedures to cope with policy and standard established by Head Office, and to follow up the revision of System Security Policies and Guidelines;
Design, develop and update IT risk management framework, policies and controls taking into consideration the bank’s strategy, current/future regulatory requirements and emerging risk scenario; Communicate IT risk management standards, policies and procedures to stakeholders of bank;
Assess the potential cybersecurity impact of emerging technologies and innovations, and include known risk and issues;
To delegate the assignments and supervise subordinates in overall daily security control operations of all systems.

Essential Functions

Perform assigned tasks in a correct and timely manner;
Always observe compliance of policies and procedures;
Monitor and make recommendations for process improvement;
Provide covers all activities related to System Security Control team members.

Competencies

We are looking for an individual who sets challenging individual or Team targets to contributes to our customer, organization and Section, and has strong motivation to achieve the targets;
Enhances internal and external network and acquires knowledge for executing deals and tasks;
Nurtures the performance and potential of juniors by providing regular feedback/guidance.

Work experience, education and skills

Bachelor degree in computer science or IT;
Minimum 5 years related experience in Cybersecurity;
Supervisory experience is essential;
Familiar with Windows Serve installation and security administration, Windows Active Directory, Domain Group Policy, DBMS administration (MSSQL, Oracle, etc), networking device and firewall configuration and administration and practical experience for those setting and monitoring;
Proficiency in English and Cantonese;
Holding professional level qualification that are specified in HKMA Enhanced Competency Framework on Cybersecurity (ECF-C).

Application

Please indicate your current and expected salary on CV for the application.

 Mizuho Bank, Limited

Mizuho Bank, Ltd. in Hong Kong is an integral part of the Japan-based Mizuho Financial Group, Inc. (NYSE: MFG). The Mizuho group is a global financial services leader with offices in nearly 40 countries, approximately 60,000 employees, and assets of almost USD 2 trillion. Mizuho provides expertise in retail banking, corporate finance, investment banking, asset management, capital markets, and sales and trading, to help businesses develop and find new opportunities for growth. To learn more: www.mizuhogroup.com

Personal data collected will be kept in strict confidence, and will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Major Responsibilities


Participate in the development and maintenance of corporate-wide information security framework, policy, guideline, standard, and operation procedures with reference to ISO27001 standard and applicable best practices;
Perform day-to-day security administration and operation including but not limited to management of end users and privileged accounts, keys and certificates, review of security logs, performance of technical vulnerability assessment and penetration testing as well as handling of security incidents, etc.;
Assess and recommend information security control measures, as well as monitor the implementation for major projects;
Participate in the implementation of security solutions and infrastructure collaborating with internal teams and external service providers;
Monitor and analyse security events for detection, investigation and response to potential security issue;
Maintain and monitor appropriate computer and network access controls, data, and physical security to ensure no security exposure;
Participate in cyber threat intelligence analysis when required
Assist to define information security risk indicators; collect, analyse and interpret the corresponding statistics for assisting senior management in overseeing information security risk;
Identify control gaps, review the residual risk level and make recommendation for risk treatment;
Interpret security key risk statistics for reporting to senior management on regular basis
Promote security awareness and ensure compliance with applicable security standards
Review and make recommendation on using of Open Source Software (OSS) and freeware
Execute security operation procedures in accordance with the corporate information security policy and guidelines when required
Keep abreast of technological knowledge in managed area of responsibility, and provide recommendations for adaptation of new security technologies and standard with reference to prevailing industry best practices
Perform other job duties as assigned by the supervisors

Requirements

University degree preferably in information technology, information security or related discipline
Minimum 4 years of experience in information security or related field
Knowledge in security practices and standards commonly adopted by the banking/financial industry such as the Cyber Resilience Assessment Framework (C-RAF), SWIFT Customer Security Controls Framework (CSCF), ISO27001 standard, etc. is an advantage;
Team player with sound interpersonal, communication and presentation skills as well as excellent problem solving and analytical skills;
Holder of security certificates - CRISC, CISA, CISM, CISSP or other equivalent certificates is an advantage
Experience and knowledge in the area of public and/or private cloud security is an advantage
Practical experience and knowledge in risk management framework and methodology is desirable
Experience in working for major financial institutions is preferred but not a must
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese
Willing to work shift duty (evening shift normally from 12:30 to 21:30 with shift duty allowance)
Candidate from non-financial industries will also be considered
Candidate with less experience may be considered for appointment as Specialist II (Information Security)

Job Description

Responsible for routine security threats discover, detection, mitigation and report following requirement from Bank of China HQ and HK Insurance Authority;
Responsible for IT security assessment, vulnerability management and risk management;
Manage IT security related policy, guideline and ensure the policies are followed by all staffs;
Responsible for IT security operational support with IT teams and external vendor.
Job Requirement

Degree or above in Computer Science, Information Technology or related fields; 
Minimum 5 years' professional experience in information security or related fields;
Sound knowledge in IT security and compliance concepts, architecture and controls;
Qualification in CISA / CISM / CISSP or equivalent security certification will be advantage;
Good understanding and experience of technologies related to cyber security, like patch management, firewall, SIEM, web application security, vulnerability scanning, data protection, security hardening etc.;
Good interpersonal and communication skill with a good command of spoken and written Chinese and English.

What will you do as a DevOps Developer?

As a devOps engineer, you will work in a well-known blockchain company. You will be responsible for the transformation of the cloud platform. implement CI/CD pipeline on development and deployment. A part from that, you will invovle in the system design including API and data flow. You will also deliver the implementation with DevOps and automation tool. In addition, you will support the security team to build a reliable system on AWS.

What is offered to you?

A competitive salary range up to 25000 to 50000 HKD per month:

* Guarantee 13 months;
* Medical and dental;
* 15 AL;
* Internal career growth plan;

What is expected of you?

* 3 years of development experience;
* Experience in CI/CD workflow and container services, eg. AWS, Docker;
* Experience in GitHub and New Relic will be a plus;
* Good communication in English;

Where are you going to work?

The office is located at Tsim Sha Tsui. This blockchain company has developed a application that connect people to digital assets, mobile payments, and DeFi services. You can also find their token on the well-known crypto currency plateform. The team you will be working in is a heavily scrum oriented team with daily stand-ups to share their and your progress. All your colleagues are smart and energetic.

Learn more or apply directly?

Does the job suit you well and do you want to start a new challenging job? If you want to apply directly, click on the 'Apply' button. Not sure if the vacancy fits your experience and wishes? Feel free to contact me for more information about this vacancy and/or other possibilities, you can contact me via + 852 3511 6201 or mail me at cheryl.ng@ambitiouspeople.com.

Scope of Duties: 

Work collaboratively and in strong partnership with Learning and Development Manager/ Line Managers/ Local HR to drive HAECO Group talent management initiatives, e.g. succession planning;
Lead and manage the talent management team;
Manage and support the development and delivery of talent initiatives;
Nurture the High Flyers within the relevant business area and use existing talent frameworks to support their growth;
Leverage data from SuccessFactors to provide insights and help inform decisions;
Identify and develop competency assessment models for talent development;
Perform other relevant duties as assigned

Requirements: 

Degree in Training & Development, Human Resources Management or related discipline;
5 years of relevant experience in a sizable organization;
Advanced project management skills, data savvy, and strong systems thinking and understanding;
Proficiency in MS Office applications e.g. PowerPoint, Excel, and Chinese Word Processing
Strong supervisory skills and analytical abilities;
Good team player and people skills to develop rapport with line managers and all levels of employees;
Positive attitude and able to deal with multi-tasks effectively;
Excellent command of English and Chinese, both spoken and written. Fluency in Putonghua

How to Apply:

Please send your resume with expected salary, quoting the employer's reference no., to: Human Resources Department - Resourcing Team, Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Company Limited, 80 South Perimeter Road, Hong Kong International Airport, Lantau, Hong Kong OR submit your application via https://careers.haeco.com/hkg/job-openings/

Candidates not contacted 4-6 weeks after submission of applications and/or interviews may consider their application unsuccessful.

All information provided by candidates will be treated in strict confidence and will be used for employment purpose only.

Scope of Duties: 

Work closely with Assistant Manager, Group Talent Management;  
Engage in talent review, succession planning and performance management exercises across all HAECO Group entities; 
Manage the talent management programmes for the Group;  
Administer and maintain the Performance Management and Succession Planning systems; 
Provide regular tracking reports and relevant analysis. 
Liaise and negotiate with internal and external parties on talent development related activities;  
Perform other relevant duties as assigned 

Requirements: 

Holder of recognised degree in Human Resources or related disciplines;  
3 years of solid experience in talent management or human resources functions at sizable organisations;  
Attention to details, action-oriented and a good team player;  
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;  
Hands-on experience in SAP/ HR systems is preferred; 
Proficiency in MS Office applications e.g. Word, PowerPoint and Excel 
Excellent command of English and Chinese, both spoken and written, fluency in Putonghua will be an advantage 

How to Apply:

Please send your resume with expected salary, quoting the employer's reference no., to: Human Resources Department - Talent & Partnership Team, Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Company Limited, 80 South Perimeter Road, Hong Kong International Airport, Lantau, Hong Kong OR submit your application via https://careers.haeco.com/hkg/job-openings/

Candidates not contacted 4-6 weeks after submission of applications and/or interviews may consider their application unsuccessful.

All information provided by candidates will be treated in strict confidence and will be used for employment purpose only.

Responsibilities:

Drive strategic and ad-hoc information security and risk analyses, risk papers and risk reports with fact finding, researching and documenting activities;
Leading the development and maintenance of Group Information Security & Risk Management Strategy, Framework, Policies, Minimum Standards;
Participating in, challenging and periodically reporting upon the risks of key IT or TRBCM strategic programs and projects;
Leading risk assessments (including Data Classification, IT Risk assessments or Business Impact Assessments) on Information Security/Risk and TBCM projects and programs;
Performing scheduled/ad-hoc checks for verifying the effectiveness of the controls implemented on various technology areas;
Supporting the identification of the technology impact of and the coordination of responses to law and regulatory changes, internal & external audit reports, etc. And monitoring the follow-up on the regulatory issue solving related to technology areas;
Measuring and reporting the implementation of Information (Technology) security framework throughout the Group;
Performing and assisting in other information risk activities where the requirements arise.

Requirements:

University BSc Degree or equivalent, preferably in IT field;
Over 10 years’ experience in Financial Industry with experience on IT Audit, Risk Management or Business Continuity Management areas (Senior title will be offered with more experience)
Sound knowledge of international information security standards and regulations (e.g., SFC IT related regulations, COBIT, ISO 27001, PDPO(HK), GDPR, China Cyber Security Law)
Knowledge of retail business and/or securities trading business, and associated laws & regulations would be considered a plus;
Good analytical skills and sound judgment;
Collaboration skills and ability to work across multiple functional line and geographical locations;
Experience in Business Continuity Management & having professional education and/or multiple international certifications for Information (Technology) Security (e.g. ISC2, ISACA accreditations) would be considered a plus.

This is a great opportunity to be part of the team and get more new exposure. If you are interested in this role please send us your CV or call us on +852 2885 8318 for a further discussion.
